subSubSection.paragraph:
Collophore (
Fig. 13E
). Anterior side with 12 ciliate chaetae, including 2 distal mac, 1 apically acuminate chaeta; posterior side with 1 thicker ciliate chaeta; lateral flap with 1 smooth chaeta and 12 ciliate chaetae.

Furcula (
Figs 13F‒G
). Manubrium ventrally with formula 1, 2, 2, 2/4 (subapical), 16 (apical) ciliate chaetae and approximately 4 elongated apical scales per side; manubrium dorsally with 5 subapical ciliate chaetae; manubrial plate with 4 ciliate chaetae and 3 psp.
